label: atrioventricular nodal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the right coronary artery and supplies the atrioventricular node.
synonym: atrioventricular node branch of right coronary artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: subsegmental pulmonary artery
definition: An artery that is a branch of the segmental pulmonary artery and supplies deoxyge blood to a smaller subsegment of the lung.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: thyrocervical trunk
definition: An artery that branches from the subclavian artery and supplies the thyroid gland, neck, and upper back regions.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: septal perforating artery
definition: An artery that branches from the left anterior descending artery and supplies the interventricular septum of the heart.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: posterolateral artery
definition: An artery that branches from the right coronary artery or the circumflex artery and supplies the posterior and lateral walls of the left ventricle.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: pulmonary arteriole
definition: An arteriole that branches from the pulmonary arteries and supplies deoxygenated blood to the pulmonary capillaries and alveolar capillaries of the lungs.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: ascending pharyngeal artery
definition: An artery of the neck that branches from the external carotid artery and supplies the pharynx.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: dural artery
definition: An artery that branches from the internal carotid artery and supplies the anterior clinoid process of the dura mater.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: pericardial artery
definition: An artery that branches from the descending thoracic aorta and supplies the dorsal portion of the pericardium.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: percardiacophrenic artery
definition: An artery that branches from the internal thoracic artery and supplies the pericardium and the diaphragm.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: incisor artery
definition: An artery that branches from the inferior alveolar artery and supplies the roots and pulp of the teeth of the lower jaw. It forms anastomoses with its contralateral partner.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: intra-acinar arteriole
definition: An arteriole that branches from the pulmonary arteriole and supplies deoxygenated blood to the pulmonary capillaries in the alveoli of the lungs.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: ascending palatine artery
definition: An artery that branches from the facial artery, and branches to supply the soft palate and the palatine tonsil.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: submental artery
definition: An artery that branches from the facial artery that runs forward under the mouth, then turns upward upon reaching the chin.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: deep lingual artery
definition: An artery that branches from the lingual artery and supplies blood to the tongue itself, particularly the body and tip of the tongue. The deep lingual artery travels superiorly in a tortuous course along the under (ventral) surface of the tongue, below the longitudinalis inferior, and above the mucous membrane.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: dorsal lingual artery
definition: An artery that branches from the lingual artery and supplies the soft palate, tonsils, epiglottis, palatoglossal arch, and adjacent mucous membrane. The dorsal lingual artery runs along the upper border of the hyoid bone and anastomises with its fellow of the opposite side.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: accessory meningeal artery
definition: An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies the meninges. The accessory meningeal artery ascends through the foramen ovale to enter the cranial cavity and supply the dura mater of the floor of the middle cranial fossa and of the trigeminal cave, and to the trigeminal ganglion.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: artery of pterygoid canal
definition: An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies blood to structures in the auditory tube, tympanic cavity, and upper pharynx. The artery of the pterygoid canal courses through the pterygoid canal, a small bony canal located in the sphenoid bone of the skull.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: descending palatine artery
definition: An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies the hard and soft palate.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: left anterior descending artery
definition: An artery that branches from the left coronary artery and supplies the anterior wall of the left ventricle, the interventricular septum, and the apex of the heart.
synonym: anterior interventricular branch of left coronary artery
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: anterior humeral circumflex artery
definition: An artery that branches from the axilliary artery and supplies the deltoid, biceps brachii, and coracobrachialis muscles, the glenohumeral joint, the proximal humeral head, and the skin overlying the anterior aspect of the proximal humerus. This artery courses laterally across the anterior surface of the humerus and anastomoses with the posterior humeral circumflex artery.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

label: posterior humeral circumflex artery
definition: An artery that branches from the axilliary artery and supplies the deltoid, teres major, teres minor, and long and lateral heads of the triceps brachii muscles, glenohumeral joint, and the cutaneous supply to the area posterolateral to the proximal humerus. This artery courses posteriorly with the axillary nerve, through the quadrangular space, to the posterior aspect of the humerus and anastomoses with the anterior humeral circumflex artery.
creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489
